values:
Tis the season
For me to move....yet again, I really seem to be making this a pattern in my life. Always on the go. I'm sad to leave my little apartment and my new friends. I am, however, excited to have a new apartment and new friends. It's a lonely nomadic existence I lead. 
I'm dating a boy. He lives far away. I like him. alot. I don't ever talk about it. I like it that way. So when we break up...it won't be a big messy affair =) I'm kidding...sort of..I guess. I don't know.
Moving is hard. It's not like I can just be like "oh yeah I'll come look at the apartment this afternoon." I actually have to plan out a day to drive my ass to Seattle to look around and with the rain and crap I'm not liking it one bit. Plus money is super super tight and I only have 3 weeks to figure it all out. Slightly stressed out. Ciao

It's been a long time.
Strange the way I feel lately. 
Empty I guess. But not empty the way you may be thinking.
Not empty as in void, like something is missing. 
Just missing feelings of want and angst and desire.
maybe satisfied???
Maybe Sunyata?
Calm.
balanced.
Boring even.
Anyways going out with Anika tonight. Can't wait. Should be fun.
I got my new tattoo started, can't wait to get it finished. 
k 
thats enough. My attention span is too short right now
ciao

You know, dating someone has really made me come to the conclusion that I ENJOY being single. And I don't view being single as the absence of a mate. I really truly enjoy being by myself. I don't feel the need to cuddle or have a deep connection or allow someone to make me happy. I am doing all these things just fine on my own. Since I have been single, everything in my life has improved. The quality of my friendships, my relationship with myself, my self esteem. I feel more whole, more complete being single than I have ever felt with any guy. EVER.  Don't get me wrong, I'm not a heartless bitch who rolls her eyes at the idea of love. I've just really out grown the hopeless, all or nothing, stars in my eyes era. Love is something that is cultivated over a long long period of time. Definitely not in a week. So, I guess we'll be "breaking up"
He's totally a forever kind of guy. And me, well, I'm just not.
ciao

OOOOhhhhhhh sunshine. How I have missed you so. Since it has been nice I am trying to wake up early and enjoy it. I love it I feel like the months and months of cold are finely being thawed. I talked to Brandon the other day on his Birthday. It was so cute he was wasted and sentimental. oh I love those times. It will be nice to go home and see him again. Well not just him, everyone. You know, with out the dreaded funeral looming over our heads. This time, we'll laugh and drink, and go to the beach. And a REAL beach too. Not just a place where the ocean slams into a bunch of rocks. I am talking Hot sand, hot boys, beer, horseshoes. SUNSHINE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
I do love the cold, don't get me wrong, but I am ready to melt the thin layer of ice enveloping my bones.
I am ready to get my butt back in school. I have been here almost a year and the outta state taxed won't be an issue anymore. Then just a few more classes and I can get the hell outta Fred Meyer. The hell outta Bellingham and the hell outta Washington....No offense.
I cleaned my carpets today. It was pretty disgusting. No seriously. DISGUSTING.
anyways I'm gonna go enjoy whats left of the sunshine.
Annika, I miss you. We should hang out soon. ANd not starting at Midnight.
beer is good
and all that jazz
ciao

I am feeling peaceful and positive right now.
I've been very pensive the past few days. 
but i feel decent right now

I am soooooo tired. Jamie and I sat up until past 5 am sharing stories about Jeremiah. All the funny, stupid, sad things that only seem to have any meaning once the said person is dead.I have been suffering from anxiety all day. You know that tight feeling in your chest. The one that makes it so hard to breathe. It's going to be an open casket funeral. That should be interesting and hard. You know I was flying here last night and I was lucky enough to have a window seat on my flight. I was looking out the window at teh stars and I just started crying. Let me tell you, you haven't seen the stars unless you've seen them from 35 thousand feet in the air. It was amazing and very appropriate. I am feeling very strange right now, so I'm gonna go and mourn.
BTW- it is soooooo sunny and warm and amazing. I miss this place.
Also- I  amhaving dinner with Brandon tonight.

I am going home tomorrow to L.A
but not for fun. Not for pleasure.
I am going home to bury one of my best friends.
i am not happy
I am going home now to sit in the dark
you would die if you knew me.

so it's been awhile. Again. 
Things are fine and wierd. Brandon has turned into this strange angry guy. I would love to just give him a hug and tell him it's ok. Things get better. You don't always have to protect yourself. *sigh* Been thinking about things lately. Which is a good sign beacuse for a while I was living in a world lacking of mental stimulation. Oh by the way, whats up with the preganancy dreams....wierd... No seriously I have one almost every other night for the past couple weeks. Strange creepy and UNINVITED!!!!!!!!!!! go away silly dreams. anyways hope to go out soon.

I miss everyone.
Lets hang out. 
soon. 
Annika, are we working together soon?
Damn I really need to get a computer. Quick. Just thought I'd stop in and see what everyone was up to these days...who's gonna be my valentine????

So it's been awhile. Feels like a lifetime.
You know what I mean.
AAAAGGGGHHHHHHHHHHHHHAAAAAAAAAAAAAGHHHHHHHHH!
Anyways I love living in my place and you guys are welcome whenever you like. I am getting sick of retail. Seriously how can people be so rude? I don't understand where it comes from. I have never seen people(especially, mostly) old people be so incredibly crass. Yeah not only are they rude but they buy astoglide. Old rude people who buy astroglide. WTF? I think I need a vacation. Maybe. And whats up with little  gangster boys who wear red bandanas, trying to terrorize myself and my fellow employees???? OOOh Mr. Bloods guy I'm soooooo scared. I shit pieces of turd tougher than that guy. WTF? And whats up with the guys here? Grow a pair. Seriously.
 I need to get the fuck outta this town. For a little while at least. I need the blue sky and fresh air of my darlin L.A. I miss my friends. I miss the smog and traffic. I miss Bar Sinister, I miss the Roxy and the Whiskey. I miss IN and OUT. I miss Melrose. I miss Cal Arts parties on thursdays. I miss Fox Run Circle, the helicopter pad. Backpack disguises. I love my new town and my new friends. I REALLY do. But I'm homesick.

I love being home.
At night though, I have a hard time turning off all the lights to go to bed. It takes me about an hour to actually GET to bed. I keep hearing all these sounds and stuff and it's scary. The first morning I woke up and I was like

So, I ran into my first love on Myspace. Wierd I haven't seen or heard from him in like 5 years. We went out for a year. I was so love. I hadn't thought of him in such a long time. It's ok though. Sometimes you have to just have to make an ass of yourself. Eh-whatever.
So Brandon told me he broke up with is girlfriend...It didn't affect me the way I though it would. I thought it would make me happy and hopeful. But no. Thats not the case. I've moved on. And this only proves it. Now I can start thinking about other stuff. We'll still be friends I'm sure. 
So I like that guy. But I don't really want to see him. I guess I feel like if nothing happens with the relationship, nothing bad can happen. Hahaha what a dork. I dunno. I just like having this crush in my own mind. Then I can make it whatever I want it to be. I once had a long love affair with a guy I'd never met. I'm kidding. I am so not the "sit on the sidelines" kind of girl. I will dive head first into anything I am passionate about. Blah blah blah. I'm fuckin tired and delirious. I'll come back and write more on a day when I can actually form thoughts and sentences without dozing off halfway through. So....

So I drank too many red bulls and sparks last night, which in turn resulted in me only getting four hours of sleep. I have been up since the disturbing and sickening hour of 7.  AAAAAAGGGGGGGGGHHHHHH
Anyways Last night we hit caps and the shoe and a charming evening full of good drinks, good music and good company.You know, if you really take the time to genuinely listen to people when they talk, you'll find that people really are quite unique and quite beautiful. Like if you actuall STOP and listen with just the intent of listening, instead of waiting to talk, you'll find you will be quite fulfilled. 
Bellingham is really starting to grow on me and I am really happy that I have moved up here. I think I have been approaching it with a more open mind since I have let go of LA. Thats the only way to move on ya know. Let go of whatever's holding you back. 
Anyways...I am looking for an apartment. One bedroom, Anyone know of any place????????????????

So, I hung out with *Waldo last night. That was fun. We watched one of my all time favorite movies. We cuddled a little bit, and to my dissapointment, he was a perfect gentleman. teehee. Um, I hate liking people.It kinda freaks me out. But on the other hand it feels really good to know that I've not been permanently scarred from previous relationships and I can healthily move away from the past. Speaking of which. Seeing and hearing about other people going through break ups make me feel really proud of the way I have handled things. I Mourned, I cried, I got angry. I stayed chaste and I really allowed myself to feel the pain of the break up, and once that got old I started doing the next thing and probably the hardest thing of all...I let go. and Now I feel healthy and whole and all in all really good about myself. Cheers to the natural process of grieving. 
It's been a long time since I've been able to say this but I am really content with my life right now. I like where I am at, and I like that my happiness is not dependent on whether or not *my other half* is happy.I am good. all by myself....
Now, if you'll excuse me, I have to go find another boyfriend!!!! lol




Totally just kidding

Punishing violence with violence is utterly futile and hypocritical. In doing so it internalizes violence throughout society. Conditioning it into all of our hearts. When we put people in prison, it should serve not only as a punishment, but as an oppurtunity for rebirth, for growth. When we return inmates back onto the streets, we should not return them as tense, angry, abused, resentful beings. They should be returned after being " reformed" and finding inner peace, spiritual understanding and self awareness. Only then has prison served any real purpose to mankind other than temporarily sheltering a ball of angry disturbed energy. Prisoners should be taught meditation and mindfullness, not be left to dwell in a spiritually barren hell. This will only continue to perpetuate the cycle of violence. Of course, mindfullness and self awareness cannot transform a criminal overnight; but it can furnish a crucial turning point with tools for understanding and transforming karma, detoxifying and leading a more peaceful life upon release.
And as for rapist and murders...well, let em rot! lol
